    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elastic scattering of beam electrons from a sample in a direction approximately opposite to that of the incident radiation. Backscattered electron (BSE) imaging is a technique used in examination of archaeological artifacts to make surfaces of materials visible.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
